                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d611">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.4731/194: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Sydney</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Moffat</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sydney</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-10-27T11:00:00+10:00"
                            >October 27, 1936—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 28—7 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Government’s trade diversion is to be debated in Parliament November 4th and 5th.
                    Every indication points to approval by substantial majority.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moffat</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
